description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to provide a permanent post on a busy Ear, Nose and Throat, Maxillofacial surgical ward. Our ward has 24 beds and undertakes a wide variety of p ENT/MaxFax surgical procedures plus Tracheostomies and Laryngectomies. We are looking for a hard working, flexible member of health care assistant to work within our friendly and supportive team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicants will work within their teams to provide a high quality, safe care environment, for patients with a range of conditions as well as elective and emergency surgery. Above all we are looking for someone who is passionate and committed to providing safe, quality care with patient dignity and respect at the forefront. We have a fantastic team, so if you would be interested in becoming part of this, please contact us for more information or apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameShiny George, Senior Sister, Billericay Ward. 01245 516270Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
